  <bodyText><![CDATA[<div class="g12">
<div class="white_box_shadow"><img id="top" src="/media/13048810/family_ski.jpg" alt="Term Time Holidays" rel="900,430" /></div>
<div> </div>
<div class="white_box_shadow">
<p>A lot of families have been asking questions recently about the consequences of taking their children out of school during term-time, following the Jon Platt High Court Victory.</p>
<p>Latest updates suggest that the following councils in England have recently dropped any legal proceedings against parents:</p>
<ul>
<li>Derby</li>
<li>Devon</li>
<li>Dudley</li>
<li>Portsmouth</li>
<li>Sandwell</li>
<li>South Gloucestershire</li>
<li>Trafford</li>
<li>Wakefield</li>
<li>Warwickshire</li>
</ul>
<br />
<p>And the following councils have made the decision not to issue fines to parents who take their children out of school for family holidays:</p>
<ul>
<li>Bury</li>
<li>Cornwall</li>
<li>Derby</li>
<li>Dorset</li>
<li>Lambeth</li>
<li>Oldham</li>
<li>Southwark</li>
</ul>
<br />
<p>We will endeavour to continue to update this information as we hear of any further developments, to assist our customers in planning their family ski holiday.</p>
</div>
</div>]]></bodyText>
